.TH "rdmacg_register_device" 9 "rdmacg_register_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdmacg_register_device \- register rdmacg device to rdma controller.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rdmacg_register_device
.BI "(struct rdmacg_device *device "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
pointer to rdmacg device whose resources need to be accounted.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If IB stack wish a device to participate in rdma cgroup resource
tracking, it must invoke this API to register with rdma cgroup before
any user space application can start using the RDMA resources.
